--- Mike Benthin <benthin(-at-)prodigy.net> wrote:


> Re breaker; the stock wall outlet under the seatbed
> has a built in 
> breaker (15 amp curcuit), but it is not GFI.  The
> GFI breaker is a 
> separate deal you can buy that plugs into a standard
> 3-prong outlet and 
> should have good contact to the ground plug (which
> BTW, also connects to 
> the neutral white wire in breaker boxes of a house).
>  I've seen rare 
> campgrounds where there is no ground plug and these
> should be checked 
> that the NARROW side of the polarized socket is hot,
> and fixtures that 
> use nonpolarized plugs, if light bulbs, should have
> the center contact 
> of the light be the hot one (check its continuity to
> which prong and 
> mark it HOT side).
> 
